HEADWORD: Twaite
<hw>Twaite</hw> <pr>(tw⟦amac⟧t)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[Prov.
E.]</ety> <fld>(Zool.)</fld> <def>A European shad; -- called also
<altname>twaite shad</altname>. See <er>Shad</er>.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

